HEADWORD: Pinnipedia
<hw>Pin`ni*pe"di*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. So
called because their webbed feet are used as paddles or fins.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A suborder of aquatic carnivorous mammals
including the seals and walruses; -- opposed to
<contr>Fissipedia</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

